00:35:44.480 --> 00:35:46.210
in writing these three novels
and there are like a lot

00:35:46.210 --> 00:35:47.940
of things that you said
and I'm like, oh yeah!

00:35:47.940 --> 00:35:49.450
This is the same thing.

00:35:49.450 --> 00:35:54.420
So from the more experienced
perspective, what was one

00:35:54.420 --> 00:35:58.530
or more things that you
learned about writing mysteries

00:35:58.530 --> 00:36:00.420
as you wrote a lot of mysteries

00:36:00.420 --> 00:36:03.250
that you maybe didn't
know when you started?

00:36:03.250 --> 00:36:04.550
&gt;&gt; Hank Phillippi Ryan: What
are some things I learned

00:36:04.550 --> 00:36:05.850
about writing mysteries

00:36:05.850 --> 00:36:07.150
that I may not have
known when I started?

00:36:07.150 --> 00:36:09.660
You know what really
the big thing is?

00:36:09.660 --> 00:36:15.740
How difficult it is and how full
of self-doubt every writer is.

00:36:15.740 --> 00:36:18.690
I mean you heard Annie
Proulx last night, said --

00:36:18.690 --> 00:36:20.930
Annie Proulx stood up
on the stage and said,

00:36:20.930 --> 00:36:23.210
"I don't really feel
like a writer."

00:36:23.210 --> 00:36:24.550
And I thought, wow, you know,

00:36:24.550 --> 00:36:27.700
if she has doubts,
everybody has doubts.

00:36:27.700 --> 00:36:31.780
Tess Gerritsen once told me,
"With every book I hand in,

00:36:31.780 --> 00:36:33.180
I wonder if this is the one

00:36:33.180 --> 00:36:35.120
where people will
realize I'm a fraud

00:36:35.120 --> 00:36:37.060
and I don't really
know what I'm doing."

00:36:37.060 --> 00:36:38.360
Tess Gerritsen!

00:36:38.360 --> 00:36:42.210
So you are -- If you
don't have doubts,

00:36:42.210 --> 00:36:44.540
you're probably not
being very realistic

00:36:44.540 --> 00:36:46.210
about what you're writing.

00:36:46.210 --> 00:36:49.670
And if you think, wow,
this is very difficult,

00:36:49.670 --> 00:36:51.530
then pat yourself on the back

00:36:51.530 --> 00:36:53.250
because that means
you're working hard.

00:36:53.250 --> 00:36:54.740
That means you're a writer.

00:36:54.740 --> 00:36:57.420
Pat yourself on the
back for going for it.

00:36:57.420 --> 00:37:00.550
The thing that will
stop any writer is

00:37:00.550 --> 00:37:03.520
that just depressing
darkness of worry

00:37:03.520 --> 00:37:05.230
that you're not good enough.

00:37:05.230 --> 00:37:08.420
You know, that's
-- Don't do that.

00:37:08.420 --> 00:37:09.930
Just throw that away.

00:37:09.930 --> 00:37:12.880
Just go for it because you'll
never know what book you have

00:37:12.880 --> 00:37:14.250
until you do it.

00:37:14.250 --> 00:37:17.750
And worrying isn't going to
make it happen any faster

00:37:17.750 --> 00:37:20.250
and it will make your
life be much more dismal.

00:37:20.250 --> 00:37:22.490
So embrace your writing.

00:37:22.490 --> 00:37:24.100
Go for it and don't worry.

00:37:24.100 --> 00:37:25.940
It will turn out
fine, I promise.

00:37:25.940 --> 00:37:27.240
It's a Hank promise.

00:37:27.240 --> 00:37:29.610
It will turn out fine.

00:37:29.610 --> 00:37:32.310
&gt;&gt; Thank you.

00:37:32.310 --> 00:37:33.610
&gt;&gt; Hank Phillippi Ryan: Yes?

