One is I can't write
in the morning.

00:38:04.090 --> 00:38:05.390
You know, I have
colleagues who get

00:38:05.390 --> 00:38:07.140
up at the crack of
dawn and write.

00:38:07.140 --> 00:38:10.510
And if I did that, if I got
up at 5 to start writing,

00:38:10.510 --> 00:38:13.600
you'd find me at like
5:05 with my head clumped

00:38:13.600 --> 00:38:15.890
against the computer,
like dead asleep.

00:38:15.890 --> 00:38:19.740
Lee Child said, "Nothing good
ever happens before noon."

00:38:19.740 --> 00:38:22.710
And that's sort of how
I feel about writing.

00:38:22.710 --> 00:38:26.420
But in my books -- I'm an
investigative reporter,

00:38:26.420 --> 00:38:28.530
as you know, and my husband
